(1) This tool lets you run an APDU script file from external storage and send the APDU commands to eUICC.
(2) To start, create a script file <filename>.apdu (make sure you give it a .apdu extension) and push it into %1$s
"(3) File format: Empty lines are skipped. Lines containing '(', ')', or \"//\" are treated as comments and are also skipped."
(4) This tool does not support multiple .apdu files. It only picks up the first .apdu file it finds in the directory.
(5) To see execution details and responses, turn on verbose logging.
Reboot eSIM in PASS_THROUGH mode before running
Lets you run an APDU script file from external storage

This tool lets you to ping an SM-DP+ server to verify TLS handshake between LPA and SM-DP+. It does so by making an ES9.InitiateAuthentication call with an empty JSON payload.
